  "response": "Great choice! Jackson Browne has many excellent songs and albums. Here are some recommendations:\n\nSongs:\n1. \"Running on Empty\"\n2. \"Doctor My Eyes\"\n3. \"The Pretender\"\n4. \"Stay\"\n5. \"Something Fine\"\n6. \"Fountain of Sorrow\"\n\nAlbums:\n1. \"Late for the Sky\" (1974) - the album you already know and love\n2. \"Running on Empty\" (1977) - his most commercially successful album\n3. \"The Pretender\" (1976)\n4. \"For Everyman\" (1973)\n5. \"Hold Out\" (1980)\n\nIf you enjoyed the contemplative, introspective style of \"Late for the Sky\", you'll likely appreciate his earlier albums like \"For Everyman\" and \"Late for the Sky\" itself. These albums are known for their thoughtful lyrics and excellent songwriting.\n\n\"Running on Empty\" is more upbeat and rock-oriented, with a concept album about life on the road. It might offer a different side of Jackson Browne that you might enjoy.\n\nWould you like me to describe any of these songs or albums in more detail?",
